cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DB 

This paper deals with the problem of extracting geographical tags from webpages, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on human trafficking, which is a criminal activity, and proposes a method that is already being integrated into a knowledge base construction system used by law enforcement agencies. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper uses an Integer Linear Programming (ILP) model, which is a technique commonly used in optimization and constraint satisfaction problems, indicating that cs.SI (Systems and Control) could also be a relevant sub-category.
